Now BH is the rectangle A , BC , for it is
             contained by GB , BC , and BG is equal to
               A ;

Now AE is the rectangle contained by AB , BC
             , for it is contained by AB , BE , and BE is
             equal to BC ;

But the angle KBC is right; 
              therefore the angle BCG is also right, so that the
               opposite angles CGK , GKB are also right. [ I. 34 ]

But the gnomon STU was also proved to be quadruple of AK ;
                therefore four times the rectangle AB ,
                 BD is equal to the gnomon STU .

But the square on EA is also double of the square on AC ;
                therefore the squares on AE , EF are
               double of the squares on AC , CD .

Let the square on AE be subtracted from each; 
               therefore the rectangle CF , FA which remains is equal to
               the square on AB .

Let ABC be an obtuse-angled triangle having the angle BAC
             obtuse, and let BD be drawn from the point B perpendicular
             to CA produced;

Let ABC be an acute-angled triangle having the angle at B
             acute, and let AD be drawn from the point A perpendicular to
               BC ;

Let the square on GE be subtracted from each; 
              therefore the rectangle contained by BE ,
                 EF which remains is equal to the square on EH .
